WEBVTT

00:00:02.419 --> 00:00:05.700
Would you agree that we live in difficult times?

00:00:07.459 --> 00:00:12.660
Despite some advances in technology, people still must endure the ravages of war,

00:00:13.619 --> 00:00:18.579
food shortages, pestilence, and disasters of various kinds.

00:00:20.100 --> 00:00:26.179
Add to that the bitter opposition and persecution we face from those who do not yet know Jehovah.

00:00:27.140 --> 00:00:30.100
How we yearn for justice and relief.

00:00:31.059 --> 00:00:38.500
The Bible Book of Revelation figuratively quotes faithful martyrs as calling out to Jehovah

00:00:39.380 --> 00:00:46.500
until when, sovereign Lord, holy and true, are you refraining from judging and avenging our blood?

00:00:48.539 --> 00:00:51.820
Although those martyrs were told to wait a little longer,

00:00:52.859 --> 00:00:57.659
Christ Jesus makes this remarkable statement recorded at Revelation 10 verse 6.

00:00:58.619 --> 00:01:01.179
There will be no delay any longer.

00:01:02.780 --> 00:01:09.900
That's good news. The entire Book of Revelation is good news for all who love and trust Jehovah.

00:01:11.099 --> 00:01:18.459
It foretells momentous events, but we need not fear them because we know that Jehovah cares for us.

00:01:20.140 --> 00:01:26.060
The good news that Revelation contains is that all that grieves us today will soon disappear.

00:01:27.019 --> 00:01:31.819
And all of its promises center on one person, Jesus Christ.

00:01:33.019 --> 00:01:39.980
In its very first verse, this thrilling Bible Book is described as a revelation by Jesus Christ.

00:01:41.099 --> 00:01:43.819
It foretells events that occur during the Lord's day.

00:01:44.459 --> 00:01:53.260
That is, the period that began when our Lord Jesus became king in 1914 and continues until the end of his thousand year reign.

00:01:54.219 --> 00:02:00.379
And throughout Revelation, we read of Jesus' key role in destroying God's enemies,

00:02:01.340 --> 00:02:06.299
removing our suffering, and restoring earth to a paradise.

00:02:08.060 --> 00:02:10.780
These are not empty promises.

00:02:12.620 --> 00:02:18.620
Revelation 1 verse 1 declares that these things must shortly take place.

00:02:19.419 --> 00:02:23.020
What sort of things must shortly take place?

00:02:23.020 --> 00:02:26.699
What role will Jesus play in these events?

00:02:26.699 --> 00:02:30.139
And how will they bring justice and relief to us?

00:02:30.139 --> 00:02:37.340
Let's begin by considering what will happen to the world empire of false religion.

00:02:37.340 --> 00:02:40.939
Please turn to Revelation chapter 18.

00:02:41.900 --> 00:02:48.460
Revelation depicts false religion as an evil prostitute, with the name Babylon the Great.

00:02:50.060 --> 00:02:55.180
For millennium, she has ridiculed, persecuted, and killed God's people.

00:02:56.539 --> 00:03:00.219
Shamelessly, she has exploited and deceived people with lies.

00:03:01.500 --> 00:03:05.659
Her influence is strong, but that's about to change.

00:03:06.460 --> 00:03:14.379
As we begin reading at Revelation 18 verse 1, note what will happen to Babylon the Great and why?

00:03:14.379 --> 00:03:24.189
After this, I saw another angel descending from heaven with great authority,

00:03:24.189 --> 00:03:31.949
and the earth was illuminated by his glory, and he cried out with a strong voice saying,

00:03:32.909 --> 00:03:40.110
she has fallen, Babylon the Great has fallen, and she has become a dwelling place of demons,

00:03:40.110 --> 00:03:45.469
and a place where every unclean spirit and every unclean and hated bird lurks.

00:03:46.110 --> 00:03:50.430
For because of the wine of the passion of her sexual immorality,

00:03:50.430 --> 00:03:57.069
all the nations have fallen victim, and the kings of the earth committed sexual immorality with her,

00:03:57.150 --> 00:04:02.830
and the merchants of the earth became rich, owing to the power of her shameless luxury.

00:04:04.430 --> 00:04:08.349
And I heard another voice out of heaven say,

00:04:08.990 --> 00:04:13.550
Get out of her, my people, if you do not want to share with her in her sins,

00:04:13.550 --> 00:04:16.509
and if you do not want to receive part of her plagues.

00:04:17.149 --> 00:04:23.790
For her sins have massed together, clear up to heaven, and God has called her acts of

00:04:23.790 --> 00:04:28.750
injustice to mind. Repay her in the way she treated others.

00:04:29.389 --> 00:04:32.910
Yes, pay her back double for the things she has done.

00:04:33.790 --> 00:04:37.389
In the cup she has mixed, mixed a double portion for her,

00:04:38.189 --> 00:04:43.470
to the extent that she glorified herself, and lived in shameless luxury,

00:04:43.470 --> 00:04:48.509
to that extent give her torment and mourning, for she keeps saying in her heart,

00:04:49.470 --> 00:04:53.709
I sit as queen, and I am not a widow, and I will never see mourning.

00:04:54.430 --> 00:04:57.629
That is why in one day her plagues will come.

00:04:58.350 --> 00:05:05.870
Death, and mourning, and famine, and she will be completely burned with fire,

00:05:05.870 --> 00:05:09.389
because Jehovah God who judged her is strong.

00:05:11.970 --> 00:05:16.449
Babylon views herself as a powerful queen who will never be brought down.

00:05:17.410 --> 00:05:22.129
Why should she? After all, she has thrived for thousands of years,

00:05:22.850 --> 00:05:29.889
and yet a terrible destruction is coming, and it will envelop her suddenly as if in one day,

00:05:31.810 --> 00:05:37.410
what role does Jesus play in this event? Look again at verses one and two.

00:05:39.170 --> 00:05:45.329
Who announces the fall of Babylon, an angel whose glory lights up the whole earth?

00:05:47.089 --> 00:05:51.009
To whom has Jehovah given such glory to our Lord Jesus?

00:05:52.449 --> 00:05:58.529
Since 1914, Jesus has been exercising authority over the earth as king and judge.

00:05:59.810 --> 00:06:03.649
How fitting that he announces the fall of Babylon the Great.

00:06:04.769 --> 00:06:06.850
But that judgment brings with it a warning.

00:06:08.129 --> 00:06:09.170
Get out of her.

00:06:10.129 --> 00:06:16.129
Never would we want to have any part of an organization that's doomed to destruction.

00:06:17.170 --> 00:06:20.850
Jehovah detests Babylon the Great, so must we.

00:06:22.449 --> 00:06:26.129
And yet, there are many who have profited from false religion.

00:06:27.569 --> 00:06:31.569
Rulers have looked to Babylon the Great to support their policies and their wars.

00:06:32.529 --> 00:06:40.019
Merchants have benefited financially. How do they react to Babylon's surprising and sudden

00:06:40.019 --> 00:06:46.259
destruction? Let's see as we continue reading from Revelation 18 verse 9.

00:07:17.550 --> 00:07:24.029
Great city, Babylon, you strong city, because in one hour your judgment has arrived.

00:07:25.149 --> 00:07:31.949
Also, the merchants of the earth are weeping and mourning over her because there is no one to buy

00:07:31.949 --> 00:07:40.670
their full cargo anymore, a full cargo of gold, silver, precious stones, pearls, fine linen,

00:07:41.230 --> 00:07:47.790
purple cloth, silk, and scarlet cloth, and everything made from scented wood,

00:07:47.790 --> 00:07:54.910
and every sort of object made from ivory, and from precious wood, copper, iron, and marble.

00:07:54.910 --> 00:08:04.110
Also, cinnamon, Indian spice, incense, perfumed oil, frankincense, wine, olive oil,

00:08:04.110 --> 00:08:12.189
fine flower, wheat, cattle, sheep, horses, carriages, slaves, and human lives.

00:08:18.399 --> 00:08:25.680
Yes, the fine fruit that you desired has left you, and all the delicacies, and the splendid

00:08:25.680 --> 00:08:32.720
things have vanished from you, never to be found again. The merchants who sold these things,

00:08:32.720 --> 00:08:38.799
who became rich from her, will stand at a distance because of their fear of her torment,

00:08:38.879 --> 00:08:44.240
and will weep and mourn, saying, too bad, too bad the great city,

00:08:44.879 --> 00:08:51.919
clothed with fine linen, purple, and scarlet, and richly adorned with gold ornaments,

00:08:51.919 --> 00:08:59.440
precious stones, and pearls. Because in one hour such great riches have been devastated,

00:08:59.440 --> 00:09:06.399
and every ship captain, and every seafaring person, and sailors, and all those who make a living

00:09:06.399 --> 00:09:13.039
by the sea, stood at a distance, and cried out as they look at the smoke from her burning,

00:09:13.039 --> 00:09:20.320
and said, what city is like the great city? They threw dust on their heads, and cried out,

00:09:20.320 --> 00:09:28.480
weeping, and mourning, and said, too bad, too bad the great city, in which all those who had

00:09:28.720 --> 00:09:35.919
ships at sea became rich from her wealth, because in one hour she has been devastated.

00:09:39.090 --> 00:09:49.409
Too bad, too bad they cry, but what about God's servants? They have a much different reaction.

00:09:50.929 --> 00:09:57.649
Let's read on from verse 20 to see how God's servants both in heaven and on earth will react

00:09:57.730 --> 00:10:05.090
to Babylon's destruction. Notice, too, why false religion deserves such scathing judgment.

00:10:20.340 --> 00:10:28.019
And a strong angel lifted up a stone like a great new stone, and hurled it into the sea,

00:10:28.820 --> 00:10:36.419
saying, thus with a swift pitch will Babylon the great city be hurled down, and she will never

00:10:36.419 --> 00:10:43.299
be found again, and the sound of singers who accompany themselves on the heart, of musicians,

00:10:44.100 --> 00:10:51.860
of flutists, and of trumpeters will never be heard in you again, and no craftsmen who practices

